modules.description: Provides compile-time conditional evaluation of `if` and `match` expressions, substituting only the active branches. Operates on OCaml syntax trees and integrates with the ppx mechanism to influence code generation. Enables conditional compilation without affecting type inference or module dependencies, useful for feature toggles or environment-specific code paths.

Provides comparison and equality operations for unit values and constant expressions, including ordered comparisons and min/max selection. Works with unit type and custom constant expression structures used in OCaml AST manipulation. Enables precise checks and transformations during code analysis or rewriting processes.
